### Usability Principles

```
1. PROGRESSIVE DISCLOSURE
   ├─ Show only essential info at first
   ├─ Details available on tap/expand
   └─ Example: Calendar hides all amounts until tap

2. CONSISTENCY
   ├─ Same buttons = same size/color
   ├─ Same actions = same flow
   └─ Example: "Mark as paid" appears same everywhere

3. FEEDBACK
   ├─ Every action gets confirmation
   ├─ Every touch has haptic feedback
   └─ Example: Swipe confirms, toast appears

4. ACCESSIBILITY
   ├─ All text 14px+ (readable)
   ├─ Color contrast 4.5:1 (WCAG AA)
   ├─ Touch targets 48x48px min
   └─ VoiceOver/TalkBack compatible

5. MOBILE-FIRST
   ├─ No hover states (mobile can't hover)
   ├─ Buttons bottom/thumb-friendly
   ├─ Scrolling instead of pagination
   └─ Bottom navigation (not top tabs)

6. ERROR PREVENTION
   ├─ Confirmation before delete
   ├─ Undo option for 30 seconds
   ├─ Can't submit empty forms
   └─ Amount validation (no negative values)
```

