### How Payments Work

```
TRANSACTION FLOW:

User in USA:
├─ Sees: "$4.99/month" in USD
├─ Taps [Subscribe]
├─ Sends to Stripe via App Store (iOS) or Google Play (Android)
├─ Stripe charges card
├─ Stripe takes 2.9% + $0.30
│  └─ You get: $4.99 - $0.44 = $4.55
├─ Subscription renews monthly automatically
└─ User can cancel anytime

YOUR REVENUE FLOW:

100 Pro Users @ $4.99/month:
├─ Gross revenue: $499
├─ Stripe fees (2.9% + $0.30): -$15
├─ Payment processor costs: ~$2
├─ Taxes (if applicable): TBD by location
├─ Net income: ~$480/month

TAXES:
├─ USA: ~25-30% self-employment tax (if sole proprietor)
├─ OR: Create LLC (better tax structure)
├─ ├─ Consult accountant (worth $500)
├─ ├─ Can write off business expenses
├─ ├─ Better tax rate (15-20% as S-Corp)
├─ └─ Might owe quarterly estimated taxes
│
├─ EUROPE (VAT):
│  ├─ If selling in EU: must charge VAT
│  ├─ VAT: 17-27% depending on country
│  ├─ BUT: Stripe handles this automatically
│  ├─ You receive net of VAT
│  └─ Stripe remits VAT to local authorities
│
└─ CANADA:
   ├─ GST/PST applies (5-15% depending on province)
   ├─ Self-employed income tax: ~30-40%
   ├─ But many deductions available
   └─ Consult Canadian tax accountant
```

